<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="36" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="36" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="36" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName genus="Metallactus" lsidName="Metallactus" pageId="36" pageNumber="47" rank="genus">Metallactus</taxonomicName>
includes species that lack a deeply excised lateral edge of the elytra, additionally, the following characters may be useful to segregate species 
<pageBreakToken pageId="37" pageNumber="48" start="start">into</pageBreakToken>
this genus: posterior margin of intercoxal prosternal process gradually narrowing, pointed; abdomen not exposed; elytral length greater than 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of pronotum (
<bibRefCitation author="Chamorro, ML" journalOrPublisher="Caucasian Entomological Bulletin" pageId="56" pageNumber="67" pagination="201 - 206" title="On the identity of Mastacanthus Suffrian, 1852 and Sternoglosus Suffrian, 1866 and key to world genera of Pachybrachina (Chrysomelidae: Cryptocephalinae: Cryptocephalini)." volume="9" year="2013">Chamorro 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
